               <p>WILLIAM MONTRION. I was walking near <placeName id="t18300415-162-crimeloc911">St. Giles' church</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-162-crimeloc911" type="placeName" value="St. Giles' church"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-162-crimeloc911" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-162-off909 t18300415-162-crimeloc911"></join> on the 6th of April, and felt a snatch at my pocket - I turned, and saw the prisoner walking from me; I followed, and charged him with taking my handkerchief - I seized him, threw his coat open, and saw my handkerchief in his inside pocket; he said he found it, but I had had it just before.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. How far was I from you? A. Five or six yards, walking the contrary way; my pocket was turned out, and he was walking on.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-162-person1441">
